          Represents the audio header of an MP3 File, the audio header consists of a number of audio frames.
MPEGFrameHeader
          Represents a MPEGFrameHeader, an MP3 is made up of a number of frames each frame starts witha four byte frame header.
XingFrame
          In some MP3s the first frame in the file is a special frame called a Xing Frame this is used to store additional information about the file.
